This script runs on the **Slurm** workload manager. 

Here's a breakdown of the details:

* **Slurm:** A popular open-source workload manager used for managing resources on high-performance computing clusters.
* **Job Name:** "snaq_myzus"
* **Output File:**  "snaq_%A_%a.out"  (captures standard output)
* **Error File:** "snaq_%A_%a.err" (captures error messages)
* **Partition:** "short" (specifies the queue or resource pool for the job)
* **Array Task IDs:** "0-5" (runs the job 6 times, each with a different task ID)
* **Nodes:** 1 (uses a single node for the job)
* **Tasks per Node:** 40 (allocates 40 tasks to the single node)
* **Wall Time:** "2-00:00:00" (sets the maximum runtime to 2 hours)
* **Mail Type:** "ALL" (sends email notifications for all events)
* **Mail User:** "rebeclem@gmail.com" (email address for notifications)
* **Julia Version:** "1.5.3" (specifies the Julia version to use)
* **Julia Script:** "/home/rebecca.clement/90day_aphid/scripts/runSNaQmyzus.jl" (the Julia script to execute)
* **Output Log:** "net$SLURM_ARRAY_TASK_ID_30runs.screenlog" (captures output from the Julia script)
